raculous benefits.\r\n\r\nThe two immediately started collecting information about Spirulina from everywhere, and even took part in a training course, on how to grow this incredible alga. They even toured other Spirulina farms out of curiosity.\r\n\r\nIt soon became clear to them that this amazing Spirulina with its incredible qualities, were incredibly underrepresented in the health food market. Furthermore, what they found was that most Spirulina, used today was sold dried in spangles, pellets, powder, and capsules, despite the fact that fresh Spirulina is far superior.\r\n\r\nFrederic and Yannick immediately started to formulate drinks with fresh Spirulina in their kitchen. Many tests later, (to the exasperation of their kids who taste tested all the recipes), the two partners managed to prepare the perfect recipe, containing fresh Spirulina, organic fruits and Alpine herbs, creating Spiralps®, the ONLY drink on the market containing FRESH Spirulina. In addition, our Spiralps® holds another distinction, as the only Spirulina drink to utilize Spirulina, which has NEVER been heated!\r\n\r\nTheir Spirulina project became so big; they realized they could no longer make room in their lives for their project, their jobs, and their families. A decision would need to be made, therefore, in the autumn of 2011 Frederic and Yannick decided to quit their jobs to start SpirAlps, S.A.\r\n\r\n<strong>SpirAlps SA was founded in Vétroz in Valais (Switzerland). The company is supported in the canton of Valais, by <a href="http://www.theark.ch" target="_blank">The Ark Foundation</a>.</strong>\r\n<h1>The <span style="color: #339966;">Founders</span></h1>\r\nHere is the founding team. Please click on each image to get their detailed profile.\r\n\r\n[one_half]\r\n<h2><span style="color: #339966;">Yannick Lesbros</span></h2>\r\nYannick is a young 38-year old exiled mountain dweller, married and father of a charming daughter. Having no running water in his country of origin, Yannick started many years ago on a long trip. He left the snowy peaks of his "Chablais Savoyard", on foot, swam across the Lake of Geneva, and settled in what he calls "a civilized country".\r\n\r\nYannick is passionate about biology and communication, as Frederic would say, "He never stops talking". Yannick loves nature and it is why, quite naturally, that he became a fan of Spirulina from the very start.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n[/one_half]\r\n\r\n[one_half]\r\n<h2><span style="color: #339966;">Frederic Dubois</span></h2>\r\nFrederic is a young 43-year old, married father of two nice boys. Frederic is a big fan of mountaineering and nature. He is an active member of the Swiss Alpine Club and is responsible for a mountain hut, perched at 2600m, in the heart of the Alps.\r\n\r\nAlthough Frederic tried to convince Yannick to be content with growing Spirulina beside the mountain hut, making drinks, and waiting for customers... Yannick was quick to point out that it would not be profitable in the long run.\r\n\r\nTherefore Frederic, the Doctor of the team, (not a medical doctor, he is afraid of blood - but an eco-chemist with a doctorate), made it his goal, to bring his scientific knowledge to bear, on better serving the entire world with their more healthful, fresh Spirulina beverage.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n[/one_half]<!--:-->', '<!--:en-->Swiss Drink<!--:--><!--:de-->Swiss Drink<!--:--><!--:fr-->Swiss Drink<!--:-->', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'open', '', '73-revision-v1', '', '', '2013-11-27 14:00:02', '2013-11-27 14:00:02', '', 73, 'http://spiralps.ch/uncategorized/73-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
